JOHANNESBURG – Ox Nche, Jason Jenkins, Kwagga Smith, Nizaam Carr, Travis Ismaiel, Curwin Bosch and Cameron Wright have been released from the Springbok squad back to their franchises following Saturday’s Castle Lager Incoming Series Test against England in Johannesburg. READ: Kolisi earns first Test victory as Bok captain It was also confirmed that prop Trevor Nyakane has been withdrawn from the Springbok squad because of injury. He has trouble with a rib injury and did not play a part in Saturday’s victory over the English at Emirates Airline Park. The Springboks travel to Bloemfontein on Sunday afternoon where they will resume their preparations for the second international against England. Next week’s second Castle Lager Incoming Series Test between the two countries takes place at the Toyota Stadium (17h05). African News Agency